  "finding": "Layered core-claim verification routes each claim to the most independent oracle that covers it: Google Fact Check fires on the 4 viral myths it reviews; the Wikidata/Crossref provenance layer fires on authorship attributions (demonstrated 4/4 correct on Dickens/Shakespeare/Tolstoy/Twain) though it covers 0 of THIS pack's fabricated-study cases; the flagged low-independence LLM tail covers 15. Net verified 19/21, with HIGH-independence still 4 here because the pack lacks simple authorship falsehoods. Honest takeaway: the layered architecture is correct and each layer works on its claim type, but high-independence coverage is bounded by which claims the open oracles actually review."
